---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About the LangIndex project.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6">
    <p
      class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[color:var(--color-accent)]"
    >
      About
    </p>
    <h1
      class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[color:var(--color-fg-strong)] sm:text-4xl"
    >
      About LangIndex
    </h1>
    <div class="content-body mt-6">
      <p>
        LangIndex is an open source, self-hosted reference for programming
        languages. Its goal is to help developers compare languages by practical
        fit, constraints, tooling, governance, and tradeoffs.
      </p>
      <p>
        The repository is the source of truth. Content changes arrive through
        normal pull requests, with factual claims backed by official sources
        whenever possible.
      </p>
      <h2>Editorial standard</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Prefer official sources: specs, docs, release notes, governance pages.</li>
        <li>Cite claims that are not obvious from the linked official resource.</li>
        <li>Separate facts from judgment. Mark unknowns directly.</li>
        <li>Use neutral, practical language. No advocacy.</li>
        <li>Every substantial page includes a <code>lastVerified</code> date.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Stack</h2>
      <p>
        Astro, TypeScript, MDX, Astro Content Collections, Tailwind CSS,
        Pagefind for static search, Docker Compose, and Caddy on a self-hosted
        Ubuntu VM. No database. No tracking. No accounts.
      </p>
      <h2>Licensing</h2>
      <p>
        Project code is GPL-3.0. Content and data are CC-BY-SA-4.0 unless a
        page states otherwise.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
